of people on the street.

289
00:15:25,425 --> 00:15:27,327
- Right.
- Once government interferes

290
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:30,497
in private activity,
more often than not,

291
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:31,898
they make it more complex

292
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:35,202
and they move it
towards extinction.

293
00:15:38,438 --> 00:15:38,938
♪

294
00:15:48,248 --> 00:15:50,050
A lot of people are
outside of tax nets...

295
00:15:50,083 --> 00:15:51,651
- Right.
- So the state government

296
00:15:51,684 --> 00:15:53,520
has to be very genius
in trying to get taxes.

297
00:15:53,553 --> 00:15:54,721
Right.

298
00:15:54,754 --> 00:15:55,955
Flex up!

299
00:16:01,061 --> 00:16:03,030
Who really runs the streets?

300
00:16:04,564 --> 00:16:07,367
The de facto front line
of law and order

301
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,102
are area boys.

302
00:16:09,136 --> 00:16:11,471
The government tries to get
people on the street...

303
00:16:12,772 --> 00:16:14,374
like the foot soldiers.

304
00:16:14,407 --> 00:16:16,676
An area boys crew
levels street taxes on,

305
00:16:16,709 --> 00:16:18,678
well, everything...

306
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:27,354
reporting to their regional
boss, a king of boys.

307
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:36,963
Taxis, buses,
any target of opportunity

308
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:39,132
pays.

309
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:41,401
You don't depend on
government, fine,

310
00:16:41,434 --> 00:16:43,770
but you're running
your own business.

311
00:16:43,803 --> 00:16:45,472
- Right.
- So you pay a bribe

312
00:16:45,505 --> 00:16:49,008
because that's the only way
to get things done.

313
00:16:49,042 --> 00:16:53,080
Every person seems to be
tainted a little.

314
00:16:54,447 --> 00:16:57,150
Police, politicians,
business leaders,

315
00:16:57,184 --> 00:17:00,353
everybody gets
their piece of the action.

316
00:17:00,387 --> 00:17:03,723
It's a daily fact of life
in Lagos.

