00:17:34,554 --> 00:17:36,789
Kadaria Ahmed is
a progressive journalist,

328
00:17:36,823 --> 00:17:38,425
editor, and TV host

329
00:17:38,458 --> 00:17:40,593
who moderates
the presidential debates.

330
00:17:40,627 --> 00:17:42,762
Years of military rule

331
00:17:42,795 --> 00:17:45,198
meant that people
were brutalized.

332
00:17:45,232 --> 00:17:48,135
There was a fight against
thinking.

333
00:17:48,168 --> 00:17:50,036
There was an anti-intellectual
movement...

334
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:51,938
- Absolutely.
- Where you were

335
00:17:51,971 --> 00:17:54,241
punished for...
Shamed.

336
00:17:54,274 --> 00:17:56,008
- Shamed for reading...
- Yes.

337
00:17:56,042 --> 00:17:58,278
For having an education,
for aspiring to those things.

338
00:17:58,311 --> 00:18:01,381
Yeah, you saw
a decline in education

339
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:03,650
that continued for 30 years.

340
00:18:03,683 --> 00:18:05,718
The biggest obstacle
in this country

341
00:18:05,752 --> 00:18:07,520
is the political class.

342
00:18:07,554 --> 00:18:09,456
Because what we've had,
you know, in Nigeria is

343
00:18:09,489 --> 00:18:12,125
if you lose elections,
you then jump to the other party

344
00:18:12,159 --> 00:18:13,793
and you win elections,

345
00:18:13,826 --> 00:18:15,995
and then if you lose,
you go back to this other party.

346
00:18:16,028 --> 00:18:17,323
- Right.
- So it's the same people.

347
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:19,499
They're going to fight
tooth and nail

348
00:18:19,532 --> 00:18:20,800
